‚úÖ Finalized Decisions

Migration Tooling:

The Enterprise Data Delivery Pipeline (EDP) will be used for both ECM SQL and Synapse SQL Pool migrations.

This replaces earlier backup/BACPAC/ADF options.

Team Responsibilities:

ARE & DAS Teams: Execute EDP pipeline for data migration and coordinate end-to-end cut-over.

DB Engineering (Jack / Jason / Sanjay / Emily): Provide technical validation, pipeline review, and restore-time benchmarks.

itte: Install ECM v2, support integration testing, and validate post-migration functionality.

Infrastructure (AR&D): Build new SQL server, clusters, and workspace configurations in subscription 3042.

Application Team (soud / ami / Bob / Pankaj): Oversee coordination, testing, and documentation updates.

Cut-Over Plan:

One-time migration and cut-over after full testing and data parity validation.

Final sync via EDP, followed by DNS (CNAME) update to redirect the front-end.

Requires an extended maintenance window (~4‚Äì6 hours).

ADLS (Data Lake) Migration:

Two options remain under evaluation ‚Äì ADCopy or ADF.

Decision expected next week after Renderer/Madan meeting.

